<span id="dpsp-post-content-markup" data-image-pin-it="true"></span>
<p><em>Zucchini relish one of my favorite ways to use up zucchini from the garden. Considerably more flavorful than straight dill pickle relish, homemade zucchini relish is a real hit at summer barbeques.</em></p>



<p><em>When this zucchini relish is made as a canning recipe, you can preserve zucchini right on the pantry shelf for year-round eating.&nbsp; It’s also perfectly fine to make a small batch for the refrigerator, and it’ll last for several months so you can enjoy it all summer long.</em></p>


<div class="block-area block-area-before-first-image"><div class="block-save-recipe cwp-large"><div class="wpforms-container one-line save-recipe wpforms-location-save_recipe_block wpforms-render-modern" id="wpforms-27686"><form id="wpforms-form-27686" class="wpforms-validate wpforms-form wpforms-ajax-form" data-formid="27686" method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data" action="/zucchini-relish/" data-token="05d4131f78d09edafcacf31c0d465a33" data-token-time="1778603767"><div class="wpforms-head-container"><div class="wpforms-title">Save this recipe!</div><div class="wpforms-description">Get this sent to your inbox, plus get new recipes from me every week via my newsletter!</div></div><noscript class="wpforms-error-noscript">Please enable JavaScript in your browser to complete this form.</noscript><div id="wpforms-error-noscript" style="display: none;">Please enable JavaScript in your browser to complete this form.</div><div class="wpforms-field-container"><div id="wpforms-27686-field_1-container" class="wpforms-field wpforms-field-email" data-field-id="1"><label class="wpforms-field-label" for="wpforms-27686-field_1">Email <span class="wpforms-required-label" aria-hidden="true">*</span></label><input type="email" id="wpforms-27686-field_1" class="wpforms-field-large wpforms-field-required" name="wpforms[fields][1]" spellcheck="false" aria-errormessage="wpforms-27686-field_1-error" required=""></div>		<div id="wpforms-27686-field_4-container" class="wpforms-field wpforms-field-text" data-field-type="text" data-field-id="4">
