	<li id="comment-21840" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-21840" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Rebecca</b> <span class="says">says:</span>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-07-23T12:44:54-05:00">July 23, 2025 at 12:44 pm</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Can I shred the zucchini instead of cutting into 1/4 or half inch?</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-21840" data-commentid="21840" data-postid="15600" data-belowelement="div-comment-21840" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Rebecca" aria-label="Reply to Rebecca">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
	<li id="comment-21866" class="comment byuser comment-author-ashley bypostauthor odd alt depth-2 staff">
		<article id="div-comment-21866" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Ashley Adamant</b> <span class="says">says:</span>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2025-07-24T09:18:36-05:00">July 24, 2025 at 9:18 am</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Yes, that’s fine, just make sure you’re able to mix it into the vinegar thoroughly and that there’s not a matted mass of it that’s not exposed to vinegar.</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-21866" data-commentid="21866" data-postid="15600" data-belowelement="div-comment-21866" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Ashley Adamant" aria-label="Reply to Ashley Adamant">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li id="comment-3987" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-3987" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Clay</b> <span class="says">says:</span>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2023-03-10T07:10:06-05:00">March 10, 2023 at 7:10 am</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This relish sounds pretty straight forward and tasty.<br>
Could a grape leaf be used in each jar instead of Pickle Crisp to try and keep some crunchiness in the veggies?</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-3987" data-commentid="3987" data-postid="15600" data-belowelement="div-comment-3987" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Clay" aria-label="Reply to Clay">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
