	<li id="comment-3327" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-3327" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Aimee</b> <span class="says">says:</span>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2022-04-26T18:22:33-05:00">April 26, 2022 at 6:22 pm</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Is it necessary to cook the relish in the brine? Or can I just put the relish in the jars and cover with hot brine like pickles?</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-3327" data-commentid="3327" data-postid="15600" data-belowelement="div-comment-3327" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Aimee" aria-label="Reply to Aimee">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
	<li id="comment-3328" class="comment odd alt depth-2">
		<article id="div-comment-3328" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Administrator</b> <span class="says">says:</span>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2022-04-29T14:49:36-05:00">April 29, 2022 at 2:49 pm</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>This recipe has been tested by first cooking the relish in the brine so I would recommend following those instructions.</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-3328" data-commentid="3328" data-postid="15600" data-belowelement="div-comment-3328" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Administrator" aria-label="Reply to Administrator">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
